                <h1>Exploring the Themes of "The Yellow Wallpaper"</h1>
                <p>The theme of "The Yellow Wallpaper" delves into mental illness, gender roles, and the struggle for self-expression. Through the protagonist's descent into madness, the story critiques the oppressive structures imposed on women in the late 19th century. The wallpaper symbolizes both her confinement and the complexity of her identity.</p>
